OL,4,Cblind piano tuner out thousands of
OL,5,Cpounds
OL,7,FThe victim had to borrow money from
OL,8,Ffriends and family as he needed to
OL,9,Fpurchase braille software to read a
OL,10,Fstring of invoices that Stanner had
OL,11,Ffalsely created.
OL,13,FIn some instances, Stanner left the
OL,14,Fvictim with as little as half an hour
OL,15,Fto pay his demands such as asking him
OL,16,Fto pay #4000 within an hour and
OL,17,Fthreatened that he would come and take
OL,18,Fhis property if he didn't meet the
OL,19,Fdemands.
